
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  MISSION: SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS                                              ║
║  SKILL: Combined find + grep + wc                                         ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

OBJECTIVE:
Run a comprehensive diagnostic across all system reports to determine
the ship's overall status and identify the authorization code needed
to proceed to the next sector.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Analyze System Reports
────────────────────────────
The diagnostics directory contains multiple system status reports (.rpt files).
You need to:

1. Count how many reports show "STATUS: CRITICAL"
2. Find the report that contains the "ENGINEERING_AUTH" code
3. The auth code format is: ENGINEERING_AUTH_XXXX (where X is a digit)

When you find the authorization code, run:
    ./verify <code>

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

USEFUL COMMANDS:
    find . -name "*.rpt"                 Find all report files
    grep "CRITICAL" *.rpt                Search for CRITICAL in reports
    grep -l "pattern" *.rpt              List files containing pattern
    grep -r "AUTH" .                     Search recursively for AUTH
    cat file.rpt | grep "STATUS"         Extract status lines

COMBINING COMMANDS:
    find . -name "*.rpt" | xargs grep "pattern"
    grep -c "pattern" *.rpt              Count matches per file

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

When complete, you'll have finished ENGINEERING and can proceed to COMMS.

